    "text": [
        "hese days, there is an ongoing debate between people about excessive usage of computers in kids is dangerous for their health. While it is possible to claim that computers become a necessity for a young child as a part of their studies and co-curriculum activities. In this essay we shall discuss the merits and demerits of allowing usage of computers in initial stage of life of child.",
        "Firstly, nowadays there are many interactive games are available online which helps children to develop memory power. Secondly, Some YouTube videos are fruitful for learning rhymes as it comes with animation and pictures. A computer also keeps child active and updated. For instance, I was amazed when my 8 years nephew told me about \u201cChandrayan 2\u201d when I asked him where did he read about it, he said he came to know about this on internet.",
        "However, excessive use of a computer may lead to mental illness. Not only that many games are on the internet which welcomes depression, which can be ended up with committing suicide. Needless to say, it also affects their social life as they spend very less time with their parents and relatives. Also, children become lazy and stubborn. In addition, as they spend most of their time on computers, their studies will suffer. For example, as per recent studies, 89% of children who spend more than 4 hours on computers are a week in their studies.",
        "In conclusion, every aspect has merits and demerits and this is not an exception. However, moderate use of computers will be definitely beneficial for children\u2019s mental growth."
    ],
